Great, it seems we can just leave the implementations as they are. I have fixed the inline math. The problem with unescaped characters appears to be a [new feature for raw strings](https://solarianprogrammer.com/2011/10/16/cpp-11-raw-strings-literals-tutorial/) in C++11. E.g. the following will compile and print the expected string:

```
const char* test = R"doc(This is the \zeta function.)doc";
std::cout << test;
```
